<p>The geometric distribution is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Discrete_probability_distribution" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Discre=
te probability distribution">discrete probability distribution</a> that des=
cribes when the first success in an infinite sequence of <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Independent_and_identically_distributed_random_varia=
bles" title=3D"Independent and identically distributed random variables">in=
dependent and identically distributed</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Bernoulli_trial" title=3D"Bernoulli trial">Bernoulli trials</a> occ=
urs. Its <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probability_mass_function=
" title=3D"Probability mass function">probability mass function</a> depends=
 on its parameterization and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suppo=
rt_(mathematics)" title=3D"Support (mathematics)">support</a>. When support=
ed on <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 \mathbb {N} }">
