<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Memorylessness">Memorylessn=
ess</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DGeometri=
c_distribution&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: Me=
morylessness"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]=
</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Memorylessness" titl=
e=3D"Memorylessness">Memorylessness</a></div>
<p>The geometric distribution is the only memoryless discrete probability d=
istribution.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometric_distribution#cite_note-4"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> It is t=
he discrete version of the same property found in the <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponential_distribution" title=3D"Exponential distribu=
tion">exponential distribution</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:8_1-2" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometric_distribution#cit=
e_note-:8-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=3D"Page:=
 228">:=E2=80=8A228=E2=80=8A</span></sup> The property asserts that the num=
ber of previously failed trials does not affect the number of future trials=
 needed for a success.=20
</p><p>Because there are two definitions of the geometric distribution, the=
re are also two definitions of memorylessness for discrete random variables=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Geometric_distribution#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Expressed in terms=
 of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conditional_probability" title=
=3D"Conditional probability">conditional probability</a>, the two definitio=
ns are
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
