<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Applications">Applications<=
/h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DGeometric_di=
stribution&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D19" title=3D"Edit section: Appli=
cations"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</spa=
n></span></div>
<p>The geometric distribution is used in many disciplines. In <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queueing_theory" title=3D"Queueing theory">queu=
eing theory</a>, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M/M/1_queue" =
title=3D"M/M/1 queue">M/M/1 queue</a> has a steady state following a geomet=
ric distribution.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-23" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometric_distribution#cite_note-23"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>23<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stochastic_process" title=3D"S=
tochastic process">stochastic processes</a>, the Yule Furry process is geom=
etrically distributed.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-24" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometric_distribution#cite_note-24"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>24<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup> The distribution also arises when modeling the lifetime of a device=
 in discrete contexts.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-25" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometric_distribution#cite_note-25"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>25<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup> It has also been used to fit data including modeling patients sprea=
ding <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/COVID-19" title=3D"COVID-19">=
COVID-19</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-26" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometric_distribution#cite_note-26"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>26<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
